Title: Jurassic Park

Title: O Brother, Where Art Thou?
Synopsis: Homer's epic poem "The Odyssey", set in the deep south during the 1930's. In it, three escaped convicts search for hidden treasure while a relentless lawman pursues them.

Title: Goodfellas
Synopsis: Henry Hill and his friends work their way up through the mob hierarchy.

Title: The Passion of the Christ
Synopsis: A film detailing the final hours and crucifixion of Jesus Christ.

Title: The Untouchables
Synopsis: Federal Agent Elliot Ness sets out to take out Al Capone; because of rampant corruption, he assembles a small, hand-picked team.

Title: Schindler's List
Synopsis: Oskar Schindler uses Jews to start a factory in Poland during the war. He witnesses the horrors endured by the Jews, and starts to save them.

Title: Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy
Synopsis: Ron Burgundy is San Diego's top rated newsman in the male dominated broadcasting of the 1970's, but that's all about to change when a new female employee with ambition to burn arrives in his office.

Title: Scarface
Synopsis: In 1980 Miami, a determined Cuban immigrant takes over a drug empire while succumbing to greed.

Title: Star Trek IV: The Voyage Home
Synopsis: To save Earth from an alien probe, Kirk and his crew go back in time to retrieve the only beings who can communicate with it, humpback whales.

Title: King Kong
Synopsis: A petroleum exploration expedition comes to an isolated island and encounters a colossal giant gorilla.

Title: Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back
Synopsis: While Luke takes advanced Jedi training from Yoda, his friends are relentlessly pursued by Darth Vader as part of his plan to capture Luke.

Title: Gandhi
Synopsis: Biography of Mahatma Gandhi, the lawyer who became the famed leader of the Indian revolts against the British through his philosophy of non-violent protest.

Title: Equilibrium
Synopsis: In a Fascist future where all forms of feeling are illegal, a man in charge of enforcing the law rises to overthrow the system.

Title: From Dusk Till Dawn
Synopsis: Two criminals and their hostages unknowingly seek temporary refuge in an establishment populated by vampires, with chaotic results.

Title: Raiders of the Lost Ark
Synopsis: Archeologist and adventurer Indiana Jones is hired by the US government to find the Ark of the Covenant, before the Nazis.

Title: Back to the Future
Synopsis: In 1985, Doc Brown invented time travel, in 1955, Marty McFly accidentally prevented his parents from meeting, putting his own existence at stake.

Title: Dances With Wolves
Synopsis: Lt. John Dunbar, exiled to a remote western Civil War outpost, befriends wolves and Indians, making him an intolerable aberration in the military.

Title: Star Trek III: The Search For Spock
Synopsis: Admiral Kirk and his bridge crew risk their careers stealing the decommissioned Enterprise to return to the restricted Genesis planet to recover Spock's body.

Title: Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan
Synopsis: Kazakh TV talking head Borat is dispatched to the United States to report on the greatest country in the world. With a documentary crew in tow, Borat becomes more interested in locating and marrying Pamela Anderson.

Title: Raging Bull
Synopsis: An emotionally self-destructive boxer's journey through life, as the violence and temper that leads him to the top in the ring, destroys his life outside it.

Title: Aliens
Synopsis: The planet from Alien (1979) has been colonized, but contact is lost. This time, the rescue team has impressive firepower, enough?

Title: Hero
Synopsis: A series of Rashomon-like flashback accounts shape the story of how one man defeated three assassins who sought to murder the most powerful warlord in pre-unified China.

Title: Hot Fuzz
Synopsis: Jealous colleagues conspire to get a top London cop transferred to a small town and paired with a witless new partner. On the beat, the pair stumble upon a series of suspicious accidents and events.

Title: Leon
Synopsis: Professional assassin Leon reluctantly takes care of 12-year-old Mathilda, a neighbor whose parents are killed, and teaches her his trade.

Title: High Plains Drifter
Synopsis: A gunfighting stranger comes to the small settlement of Lago and is hired to bring the townsfolk together in an attempt to hold off three outlaws who are on their way.

Title: Collateral
Synopsis: A cab driver finds himself the hostage of an engaging contract killer as he makes his rounds from hit to hit during one night in LA. He must find a way to save both himself and one last victim.

Title: American Beauty
Synopsis: Lester Burnham, a depressed suburban father in a mid-life crisis, decides to turn his hectic life around after developing an infatuation for his daughter's attractive friend.

Title: Lethal Weapon
Synopsis: A veteran cop, Murtough, is partnered with a young homicidal cop, Riggs. Both having one thing in common, hating working in pairs. Now they must learn to work with one and other to stop a gang of drug smugglers.

Title: Lethal Weapon 2
Synopsis: Riggs and Murtaugh are on the trail of South African diplomats who are using their immunity to engage in criminal activities.

Title: Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon
Synopsis: Two warriors in pursuit of a stolen sword and a notorious fugitive are led to an impetuous, physically-skilled, teenage nobleman's daughter, who is at a crossroads in her life.

Title: Brokeback Mountain
Synopsis: Based on the 'E. Annie Proulx' story about a forbidden and secretive relationship between two cowboys and their lives over the years.

Title: Hulk
Synopsis: A geneticist's experimental accident curses him with the tendency to become a powerful giant green brute under emotional stress.

Title: Sense and Sensibility
Synopsis: Rich Mr. Dashwood dies, leaving his second wife and her daughters poor by the rules of inheritance. Two daughters are the titular opposites.

Title: Ride with the Devil
Synopsis: Jake Roedel and Jack Bull Chiles are friends in Missouri when the Civil War starts.

Title: Twins
Synopsis: A physically perfect, but innocent, man goes in search of his twin brother, who is a short small-time crook.

Title: 28 Days Later…
Synopsis: Four weeks after a mysterious, incurable virus spreads throughout the UK, a handful of survivors try to find sanctuary.

Title: The Beach
Synopsis: Twenty-something Richard travels to Thailand and finds himself in possession of a strange map. Rumours state that it leads to a solitary beach paradise, a tropical bliss - excited and intrigued, he sets out to find it.

Title: Trainspotting
Synopsis: Renton, deeply immersed in the Edinburgh drug scene, tries to clean up and get out, despite the allure of the drugs and influence of friends.

Title: The Spy Who Loved Me
Synopsis: James Bond investigates the hijacking of British and Russian submarines carrying nuclear warheads with the help of a KGB agent whose lover he killed.

Title: Downfall
Synopsis: Traudl Junge (Lara), the final secretary for Adolf Hitler (Ganz), tells of the Nazi dictator's final days in his Berlin bunker at the end of WWII.

Title: Letters from Iwo Jima
Synopsis: The story of the battle of Iwo Jima between the United States and Imperial Japan during World War II, as told from the perspective of the Japanese who fought it.

Title: Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan
Synopsis: Admiral Kirk's midlife crisis is interrupted by the return of an old enemy looking for revenge and a potentially destructive device.

Title: House of Flying Daggers
Synopsis: A romantic warrior breaks a beautiful member of a rebel army out of prison to help her rejoin her fellows, but things are not what they seem.

Title: Das Boot
Synopsis: The claustrophobic world of a WWII German U-boat; boredom, filth, and sheer terror.

Title: Casino Royale
Synopsis: In an early spy spoof, aging Sir James Bond (David Niven) comes out of retirement to take on SMERSH.

Title: Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope
Synopsis: Luke Skywalker leaves his home planet, teams up with other rebels, and tries to save Princess Leia from the evil clutches of Darth Vader.

Title: E.T.: The Extra-Terrestrial
Synopsis: A group of Earth children help a stranded alien botanist return home.

Title: Amelie
Synopsis: Amelie, an innocent and naive girl in Paris, with her own sense of justice, decides to help those around her and along the way, discovers love.

Title: You Only Live Twice
Synopsis: Agent 007 and the Japanese secret service ninja force must find and stop the true culprit of a series of spacejackings before nuclear war is provoked.

Title: Thunderball
Synopsis: James Bond heads to The Bahamas to recover two nuclear warheads stolen by SPECTRE agent Emilio Largo in an international extortion scheme.

Title: Alien
Synopsis: A mining ship, investigating a suspected SOS, lands on a distant planet. The crew discovers some strange creatures and investigates.

Title: On Her Majesty's Secret Service
Synopsis: James Bond woos a mob boss's daughter and goes undercover to uncover the true reason for Blofeld's allergy research in the Swiss Alps that involves beautiful women from around the world.

Title: Pulp Fiction
Synopsis: The lives of two mob hit men, a boxer, a gangster's wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

Title: Rumble in the Bronx
Synopsis: A young man visiting and helping his uncle in New York City finds himself forced to fight a street gang and the mob with his martial art skills.

Title: Diamonds are Forever
Synopsis: A diamond smuggling investigation leads James Bond to Las Vegas, where he uncovers an extortion plot headed by his nemesis, Ernst Stavro Blofeld.

Title: Fargo
Synopsis: Jerry Lundegaard's inept crime falls apart due to his and his henchmen's bungling and the persistent police work of pregnant Marge Gunderson.

Title: Live and Let Die
Synopsis: 007 is sent to stop a diabolically brilliant heroin magnate armed with a complex organization and a reliable psychic tarot card reader.

Title: The Man with the Golden Gun
Synopsis: Bond is led to believe that he is targeted by the world's most expensive assassin and must hunt him down to stop him.

Title: Good Night, and Good Luck
Synopsis: Broadcast journalist Edward R. Murrow looks to bring down Senator Joseph McCarthy.

Title: Pale Rider
Synopsis: A mysterious preacher protects a humble prospector village from a greedy mining company trying to encroach on their land.

Title: The Terminator
Synopsis: A human-looking, apparently unstoppable cyborg is sent from the future to kill Sarah Connor; Kyle Reese is sent to stop it.

Title: Around the World in 80 Days
Synopsis: Adaptation of Jules Verne's novel about a Victorian Englishman who bets that with the new steamships and railways he can do what the title says.

Title: The Usual Suspects
Synopsis: A boat has been destroyed, criminals are dead, and the key to this mystery lies with the only survivor and his twisted, convoluted story beginning with five career crooks in a seemingly random police lineup.

Title: Memento
Synopsis: A man, suffering from short-term memory loss, uses notes and tattoos to hunt for the man he thinks killed his wife.

Title: Shaun of the Dead
Synopsis: A man decides to turn his moribund life around by winning back his ex-girlfriend, reconciling his relationship with his mother, and dealing with an entire community that has returned from the dead to eat the living.

Title: Four Weddings and a Funeral
Synopsis: Comedy-drama about a group of British friends... the title says the rest.

Title: Night Watch
Synopsis: A fantasy-thriller set in present-day Moscow where the respective forces that control daytime and nighttime do battle.

Title: Goldfinger
Synopsis: Investigating a gold magnate's gold smuggling, James Bond uncovers a plot to contaminate the Fort Knox gold reserve.

Title: The Lives of Others
Synopsis: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police, conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover, finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.

Title: From Russia with Love
Synopsis: James Bond willingly falls into an assassination ploy involving a naive Russian beauty in order to retrieve a Soviet encryption device that was stolen by SPECTRE.

Title: Reservoir Dogs
Synopsis: After a simple jewelery heist goes terribly wrong, the surviving criminals begin to suspect that one of them is a police informant.

Title: Dr. No
Synopsis: James Bond's investigation of a missing colleague in Jamaica leads him to the island of the mysterious Dr. No and a scheme to end the US space program.

Title: King Kong
Synopsis: A film crew goes to a tropical island for an exotic location shoot and discovers a colossal giant gorilla who takes a shine to their female blonde star.

Title: Seven Samurai
Synopsis: A poor village under attack by bandits recruits seven unemployed samurai to help them defend themselves.

Title: Super Size Me
Synopsis: An irreverent look at obesity in America and one of its sources - fast food corporations.

Title: Kagemusha
Synopsis: When a powerful warlord in medieval Japan dies, a poor thief recruited to impersonate him finds difficulty

Title: Ran
Synopsis: An elderly lord abdicates to his three sons, and the two corrupt ones turn against him.

Title: Sunshine
Synopsis: A team of astronauts are sent to re-ignite the dying sun 50 years into the future.

Title: Once Were Warriors
Synopsis: A family descended from Maori warriors is bedeviled by a violent father and the societal problems of being treated as outcasts.
